# Create Product Design Spec (Project Overlay)

The full skill — six-question framework, UX surfaces, ambiguity / error states — is in the `praxis` plugin's `create-product-design-spec` skill. Read it first.

## Project-specific paths

- Lives at: `{{paths.waves}}/wave-NNN-<slug>/product-design.md`
- Personas referenced: `{{paths.product}}/use-cases.md`
- Existing wave designs to read for tone: any closed wave under `{{paths.waves}}/`
- Thin-slice template: `.github/instructions/thin-slice-template.md` (copied from the plugin)

## Project-specific gates

- Authored or owned by the product designer (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product-designer}}.agent.md`).
- Must be approved by the product manager (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product-manager}}.agent.md`) before `product-architecture.md` is finalized.
- Acceptance criteria are the single source of truth for sprint test plans — they must be precise enough that the engineering persona can write Journey + Composition + Logic test cases without a follow-up question.

## UI-specific UX guidance

If the wave touches the UI, also follow `.github/instructions/{{personas.aliases.product-designer}}-designer.instructions.md` for {{stack.ui_framework}} UX patterns.
